#. (itstool) path: abstract/para
#: article.translate.xml:32
msgid "A journaling file system uses a log to record all transactions that take place in the file system, and preserves its integrity in the event of a system crash or power failure. Although it is still possible to lose unsaved changes to files, journaling almost completely eliminates the possibility of file system corruption caused by an unclean shutdown. It also shortens to a minimum the time required for after-failure file system checking. Although the UFS file system employed by FreeBSD does not implement journaling itself, the new journal class of the GEOM framework in FreeBSD 7.<replaceable>X</replaceable> can be used to provide file system independent journaling. This article explains how to implement UFS journaling on a typical desktop PC scenario."
msgstr ""

