#: article.translate.xml:48
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: sect1/para
#: article.translate.xml:50
msgid "While professional servers are usually well protected from unforeseen shutdowns, the typical desktop is at the mercy of power failures, accidental resets, and other user related incidents that can lead to unclean shutdowns. Soft Updates usually protect the file system efficiently in such cases, although most of the times a lengthy background check is required. On rare occasions, file system corruption reaches a point where user intervention is required and data may be lost."
